sql:
SELECT type_name
FROM clothing_types
WHERE is_active = 1;

SELECT type_id, SUM(quantity) AS total_inventory
FROM inventory
GROUP BY type_id;

SELECT COUNT(*) AS active_designers_count
FROM designers
WHERE is_active = 1;

SELECT type_name, description
FROM clothing_types
WHERE type_id = 1;

external_knowledge:
- "sailing smoothly" and "bureaucratic sea of approvals" are metaphors for the approval process;
- "shores of official approval" represents the official approval date;
- "actively afloat" translates to units that are currently active (is_active = 1);
- The "typical time" refers to the average time between update and approval dates.

- "Identities" refers to the unit names;
- "Shorthand notations" refers to the symbols used for these units;
- "Measurement systems" refers to the different units of measurement such as US, EU, UK, etc.

sql:
SELECT user_id, COUNT(access_id) AS access_count
FROM access_logs
GROUP BY user_id;

external_knowledge:
- "fashion weavers" refers to the designers;
- "threads woven into the fabric of current demand" refers to active designers (is_active = 1);
- "cloth size" refers to the size of the clothing;
- "holding in their looms" means the quantity of each size in stock;
- "volume of stock" refers to the total quantity of each size.

sql:
SELECT AVG(size) AS average_size, MIN(size) AS min_size, MAX(size) AS max_size
FROM size_charts
WHERE type_id = 0 AND size BETWEEN 'XS' AND 'XXL';
